definition.value: Category=sequence. Note: This isoform contains an Hx20CxCC motif--resembling a metal coordination motif--in the N-terminal region. label.value: voltage-gated potassium channel KCNC1 isoform Long phosphorylated 1

value.value: A voltage-gated potassium channel KCNC1 isoform Long phosphorylated form in which the phosphorylation occurs by the action of PKC at the Ser residue within the DSKL motif located in the C-terminal tail. In resting neurons, basal phosphorylation at this site decreases Kv3.1 channel current, reducing neuronal ability to follow high frequency stimulation. Example: UniProtKB:P25122-1, Ser-503, MOD:00046.

label.value: voltage-gated potassium channel KCNC4 isoform 2 phosphorylated 1

value.value: A voltage-gated potassium channel KCNC4 isoform 2 phosphorylated form in which the phosphorylation occurs by the action of PKC at multiple Ser residues located in the N-terminal domain. Example: UniProtKB:Q03721-2, Ser-8/Ser-9/Ser-15/Ser-21, MOD:00046.

label.value: voltage-gated potassium channel KCND2 isoform 1 phosphorylated 1

value.value: A voltage-gated potassium channel KCND2 isoform 1 phosphorylated form in which the phosphorylation occurs within the amino- and carboxyl-terminal cytoplasmic domains by cAMP-dependent protein kinase (PKA). At the N terminus, the phosporylation occurs at a Thr residue within the PKA consensus phosphorylation sequence adjacent to the first transmembrane domain (segment S1). At the C-terminus, it occurs at the conserved Ser within the motif [RQ]GS[IV]QEL. Example: UniProtKB:Q9Z0V2-1, Thr-38, MOD:00047|Ser-552, MOD:00046.

label.value: voltage-gated potassium channel KCND2 isoform 1 phosphorylated 2

value.value: A voltage-gated potassium channel KCND2 isoform 1 phosphorylated form in which the phosphorylation occurs within the amino-terminal cytoplasmic domain by cAMP-dependent protein kinase (PKA). The phosporylation occurs at a Thr residue within the PKA consensus phosphorylation sequence adjacent to the first transmembrane domain (segment S1). Example: UniProtKB:Q9Z0V2-1, Thr-38, MOD:00047.

label.value: voltage-gated potassium channel KCND2 isoform 1 phosphorylated 3

value.value: A voltage-gated potassium channel KCND2 isoform 1 phosphorylated form in which the phosphorylation occurs within the carboxyl-terminal cytoplasmic domain by cAMP-dependent protein kinase (PKA). Phosphorylation occurs at the conserved Ser within the motif [RQ]GS[IV]QEL. Example: UniProtKB:Q9Z0V2-1, Ser-552, MOD:00046.
